;\"\u003e\u0026#127963;\u0026#65039; Geopolitical \u0026amp; Fed Watch\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#34d399; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eHormuz Flow \u0026amp; Supply Chain Deflation\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDraft Narrative:\u003c/strong\u003e The briefing frames freight corridors through Hormuz as normalized under a toll-free mandate. Treat operational details as narrative unless confirmed by official statements or reliable live news flow.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eEnergy Equilibrium:\u003c/strong\u003e Brent in the draft\u0027s $77.50 to $78.50 range would limit the ability of geopolitical risk premium to feed domestic inflation.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFed Chair Warsh Watch\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eForward-Looking Paradigm:\u003c/strong\u003e Desks continue to discount backward-looking regional projections and focus on the productivity counterweight narrative.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eStrategic Ambiguity:\u003c/strong\u003e Lower Fed speech density leaves markets to price the path with fewer guideposts. Watch whether the 2-Year auction confirms demand despite that ambiguity.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Blueprint:\u003c/strong\u003e The May 1 expansion candle remains the technical lodestar. Middle East premium removal plus clean interbank pipelines keeps the runway open for structural equity exposure.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Horizons:\u003c/strong\u003e Structural projections remain mapped to the 8,447 to 8,477 year-end Wall Street High Call zone on S\u0026amp;P 500 futures.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e Monitor 1.5k MotiveWave volume charts around the 10:00 ET Richmond data and 13:00 ET 2-Year auction. Do not short all-time-high expansion; treat VAL flushes as buy candidates only when absorption confirms.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25); border-radius:8p